# Crop Proteome Atlas — Storage Protein Analysis

Structured Python workflow for the analysis of storage protein expression across tissues in crop species.

## Overview
This repository contains analysis code developed as part of the Crop Proteome Atlas project, funded by the Elite Network of Bavaria. The project comprises large-scale proteomics datasets covering ~100 crop species, with an average of 15 tissues per species.

This work focuses on the distribution and abundance of storage proteins across tissues in cereal crops, with relevance for their techno-functional properties.

## Features
- Integration of proteomics datasets across multiple tissues and species  
- Orthology-based mapping of proteins across crop species  
- Extraction and analysis of storage protein families  
- Tissue-specific expression profiling across cereal species  
- Generation of summary statistics and visualisations  

## Technical Highlights
- Developed in Python (pandas, numpy, matplotlib, seaborn)  
- Structured workflow for handling large multi-tissue proteomics datasets  
- Designed for reproducible and scalable data analysis  
- Compatible with Linux/HPC environments  

## Scope of the repository
- Analysis of storage protein expression across ~10 cereal crop species  
- Integration of orthology information with quantitative proteomics data  
- Exploration of tissue-specific protein distribution patterns  
